<%
  var pageTitle   = 'The Nest — Lizzyland';
  var pageDesc    = 'Your space is always speaking. Make it say something beautiful.';
  var currentPage = 'nest';
%>
<%- include('partials/header') %>

<style>
  /* ── Hero ── */
  .ll-nest-hero {
    position: relative; min-height: 220px;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    overflow: hidden; background: var(--ocean);
  }
  .ll-nest-hero-img {
    position: absolute; inset: 0;
    width: 100%; height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover; object-position: center 40%;
  }
  .ll-nest-hero-overlay {
    position: absolute; inset: 0;
    background: linear-gradient(to top, rgba(45,27,14,0.82) 0%, rgba(26,138,122,0.3) 55%, rgba(200,149,42,0.08) 100%);
  }
  .ll-nest-hero-inner {
    position: relative; z-index: 2;
    max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto;
    width: 100%; padding: 2.5rem 2rem; color: var(--white);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .ll-nest-hero-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-accent); font-style: italic;
    font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--gold-light);
    letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase;
    opacity: 0.8; margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }
  .ll-nest-hero-inner h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.2rem);
    color: var(--white); margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
    text-shadow: 0 2px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
  }
  .ll-nest-hero-inner p {
    font-family: var(--font-accent); font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.1rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85) !important; margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Intro ── */
  .ll-nest-intro {
    padding: 4rem 2rem 3rem;
    background: var(--sand-light); text-align: center;
  }
  .ll-nest-intro-inner { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .ll-nest-intro h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.4rem);
    color: var(--warm-dark); margin-bottom: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600;
  }
  .ll-nest-lead {
    font-family: var(--font-accent); font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--text-soft); line-height: 1.85;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .ll-nest-lead-body {
    font-size: 0.97rem; color: var(--text-soft);
    line-height: 2; max-width: 580px; margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* ── Magazine sections ── */
  .ll-nest-section { padding: 2.8rem 2rem; }
  .ll-nest-section:nth-child(odd)  { background: var(--cream); }
  .ll-nest-section:nth-child(even) { background: var(--sand-light); }

  .ll-nest-inner {
    max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem; align-items: start;
  }
  .ll-nest-inner.reverse { direction: rtl; }
  .ll-nest-inner.reverse > * { direction: ltr; }

  .ll-nest-img-block { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
  .ll-nest-img {
    width: 100%; border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    object-fit: cover; aspect-ratio: 4/5;
    box-shadow: 0 12px 48px rgba(0,0,0,0.12);
    display: block;
  }
  .ll-nest-caption {
    margin-top: 0.85rem;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    background: rgba(26,138,122,0.06);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--ocean);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius-sm) var(--radius-sm) 0;
    font-size: 0.76rem; font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .ll-nest-eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    color: var(--gold); margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .ll-nest-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem);
    color: var(--warm-dark); font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }
  .ll-nest-tagline {
    font-family: var(--font-accent); font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--ocean);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .ll-nest-body {
    font-size: 0.97rem; color: var(--text-soft);
    line-height: 2; margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
  }
  .ll-nest-body p { margin: 0 0 0.85rem; }
  .ll-nest-body p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .ll-nest-benefits {
    list-style: none; margin-bottom: 2rem;
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 0.35rem 1.5rem;
  }
  .ll-nest-benefits li {
    font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-soft);
    padding: 0.3rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--sand-deep);
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.4rem;
  }
  .ll-nest-benefits li::before { content: '✦'; color: var(--gold); font-size: 0.55rem; flex-shrink: 0; }

  .ll-nest-cta {
    display: inline-block; background: var(--ocean);
    color: var(--white) !important; padding: 0.8rem 2.2rem;
    border-radius: 50px; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
  }
  .ll-nest-cta:hover { background: var(--gold); transform: translateY(-2px); }

  /* ── Free solves strip ── */
  .ll-nest-freesolves {
    padding: 3.5rem 2rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--ocean) 0%, #0d6b5e 100%);
  }
  .ll-nest-freesolves-inner { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; text-align: center; }
  .ll-nest-freesolves-eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    color: var(--gold-light); margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .ll-nest-freesolves h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.2rem);
    color: var(--white); font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .ll-nest-freesolves-intro {
    font-family: var(--font-accent); font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8);
    max-width: 580px; margin: 0 auto 2.5rem; line-height: 1.85;
  }
  .ll-nest-tips-grid {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem; text-align: left;
  }
  .ll-nest-tip-card {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: 1.4rem 1.25rem;
  }
  .ll-nest-tip-number {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.6rem; color: var(--gold-light);
    opacity: 0.5; font-weight: 700;
    display: block; margin-bottom: 0.4rem; line-height: 1;
  }
  .ll-nest-tip-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1rem; color: var(--white);
    font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .ll-nest-tip-body {
    font-size: 0.84rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.72);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  /* ── Philosophy strip ── */
  .ll-nest-philosophy {
    padding: 3rem 2rem;
    background: var(--sand-light);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .ll-nest-philosophy-inner { max-width: 620px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .ll-philosophy-quote {
    font-family: var(--font-accent); font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.2vw, 1.45rem);
    color: var(--warm-dark); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .ll-philosophy-byline {
    font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--gold); font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ── Door bridges ── */
  .ll-door-bridges {
    padding: 3rem 2rem;
    background: var(--cream);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .ll-door-bridges-intro {
    font-family: var(--font-accent); font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text-soft);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .ll-door-bridge-grid {
    max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }
  .ll-door-bridge-card {
    background: var(--white);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: 1.75rem 1.5rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    border: 1px solid var(--sand-deep);
    transition: all 0.25s;
    display: block;
  }
  .ll-door-bridge-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--ocean);
    transform: translateY(-3px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(26,138,122,0.12);
  }
  .ll-door-bridge-arrow {
    font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    color: var(--gold); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .ll-door-bridge-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--warm-dark);
    font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }
  .ll-door-bridge-desc {
    font-family: var(--font-accent); font-style: italic;
    font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* ── Affiliate disclosure ── */
  .ll-affiliate-disclosure {
    padding: 1.25rem 2rem;
    background: var(--cream);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .ll-affiliate-disclosure p {
    font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--text-muted);
    font-style: italic; max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto; line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ── Responsive ── */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .ll-nest-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; }
    .ll-nest-inner.reverse { direction: ltr; }
    .ll-nest-benefits { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .ll-nest-img { aspect-ratio: 16/9; }
    .ll-nest-tips-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .ll-door-bridge-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>

<!-- ══ HERO ══ -->
<section class="ll-nest-hero">
  <img src="/images/nest-banner.jpg" alt="The Nest — Make Your Space Beautiful" class="ll-nest-hero-img" onerror="this.style.display='none'">
  <div class="ll-nest-hero-overlay"></div>
  <div class="ll-nest-hero-inner">
    <div class="ll-nest-hero-eyebrow">✦ Happiness · Your Environment ✦</div>
    <h1>The Nest.</h1>
    <p>Your space is always speaking. Make it say something beautiful.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══ INTRO ══ -->
<section class="ll-nest-intro">
  <div class="ll-nest-intro-inner">
    <h2>Your home is not a backdrop.<br>It is a mood you live inside of.</h2>
    <p class="ll-nest-lead">
      In feng shui, your environment is considered a third skin —<br>
      after your body and your clothing, the space around you<br>
      is always in conversation with your energy.
    </p>
    <p class="ll-nest-lead-body">
      This is not about expensive renovations or starting over.<br><br>
      It is about noticing what your home is already saying — and gently, intentionally, 
      beginning to let it say something better.<br><br>
      Light. Texture. Flow. A surface cleared. A window dressed.<br>
      The small acts of curation that tell your nervous system: <em>this is a beautiful life.</em>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══ 1: LINEN CURTAINS ══ -->
<section class="ll-nest-section">
  <div class="ll-nest-inner">
    <div class="ll-nest-img-block">
      <img src="/images/joydeco-linen-curtains.webp" alt="JoyDeco Linen Light-Filtering Curtains" class="ll-nest-img" loading="lazy">
      <p class="ll-nest-caption">In feng shui, windows are the eyes of the home. How you dress them determines how energy — and light — enters your life. Linen is considered the ideal window fabric: it softens without blocking, filters without hiding, and breathes with the room rather than against it.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ll-nest-content">
      <div class="ll-nest-eyebrow">Light</div>
      <h2 class="ll-nest-title">Linen Curtains</h2>
      <p class="ll-nest-tagline">The light that enters your home is the first thing that sets the mood.</p>
      <div class="ll-nest-body">
        <p>You wake up and the room is already telling you something.</p>
        <p>Harsh, unfiltered morning light — and something in you braces before the day has even started. But soft, golden, diffused light through linen — and the room holds you a little longer.</p>
        <p>This is not a small thing. This is your nervous system, reading its environment before you've had a single thought.</p>
        <p>Natural linen softens without hiding. It lets the warmth in, quietly, on your terms. Floor-to-ceiling fabric elongates a room, creates volume, says <em>there is space here.</em></p>
        <p>Hang them high. Let them pool slightly. This is the easiest luxury you will ever buy.</p>
      </div>
      <ul class="ll-nest-benefits">
        <li>Natural linen — breathes with the room</li>
        <li>Diffuses light without blocking it</li>
        <li>Elongates walls — instant height</li>
        <li>Custom sizing — made to your window</li>
        <li>Coastal &amp; minimalist styles available</li>
        <li>Opens the feng shui energy of windows</li>
      </ul>
      <!-- JOYDECO AFFILIATE LINK — replace YOUR_REF with AWIN tracking ref once live -->
      <a href="https://joydeco.com/collections/linen-curtains?ref=YOUR_REF" class="ll-nest-cta" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Shop Linen Curtains →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══ 2: BLACKOUT BEDROOM CURTAINS ══ -->
<section class="ll-nest-section">
  <div class="ll-nest-inner reverse">
    <div class="ll-nest-img-block">
      <img src="/images/joydeco-blackout-curtains.webp" alt="JoyDeco Blackout Bedroom Curtains" class="ll-nest-img" loading="lazy">
      <p class="ll-nest-caption">Complete darkness during sleep suppresses cortisol and allows full melatonin production. Studies show even small amounts of ambient light — a street lamp through thin curtains — reduce deep sleep quality by up to 50%. The bedroom is a sanctuary. Treat it like one.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ll-nest-content">
      <div class="ll-nest-eyebrow">Rest</div>
      <h2 class="ll-nest-title">Blackout Curtains</h2>
      <p class="ll-nest-tagline">The bedroom does one job. Make sure your curtains know that.</p>
      <div class="ll-nest-body">
        <p>The sleep sanctuary begins before you get into bed.</p>
        <p>In feng shui, the bedroom is the most energetically protected room in the home — a space that belongs only to rest, restoration, and intimacy. Nothing chaotic enters here.</p>
        <p>Light is chaotic. The street lamp. The neighbour's porch. The blue dawn at 5am when your body isn't ready.</p>
        <p>True blackout is one of the highest-value upgrades you can make to your sleep — and it happens to be one of the most beautiful ones too. Velvet and thermal blackout in deep, rich tones. The room that means business.</p>
        <p>Close them. The world will still be there in the morning.</p>
      </div>
      <ul class="ll-nest-benefits">
        <li>Full blackout — no light bleed at edges</li>
        <li>Thermal insulation — cooler in summer, warmer in winter</li>
        <li>Sound dampening for lighter sleepers</li>
        <li>Velvet &amp; rich fabric options</li>
        <li>Custom sized to your bedroom window</li>
        <li>Deepens sleep quality measurably</li>
      </ul>
      <!-- JOYDECO AFFILIATE LINK — replace YOUR_REF with AWIN tracking ref once live -->
      <a href="https://joydeco.com/collections/blackout-curtains?ref=YOUR_REF" class="ll-nest-cta" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Shop Blackout Curtains →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══ 3: ROMAN SHADES ══ -->
<section class="ll-nest-section">
  <div class="ll-nest-inner">
    <div class="ll-nest-img-block">
      <img src="/images/joydeco-roman-shades.webp" alt="JoyDeco Custom Roman Shades" class="ll-nest-img" loading="lazy">
      <p class="ll-nest-caption">Roman shades are one of the oldest window treatments in recorded history — used in ancient Rome to filter dust from the Colosseum. Their clean horizontal fold creates visual order and calm, which feng shui associates with mental clarity and reduced decision fatigue.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ll-nest-content">
      <div class="ll-nest-eyebrow">Order</div>
      <h2 class="ll-nest-title">Roman Shades</h2>
      <p class="ll-nest-tagline">Clean lines. A room that thinks straight.</p>
      <div class="ll-nest-body">
        <p>There is a reason a beautifully styled room feels easier to be in.</p>
        <p>Visual noise — the tangle of mismatched fabrics, the cheap horizontal blind, the curtain rail that's been wrong since you moved in — registers as stress. Not consciously. Just quietly, constantly, underneath everything else.</p>
        <p>Roman shades are the editing of a room. They fold flat, sit neat, control light precisely. They are the clean line that lets the rest of the space breathe.</p>
        <p>In a kitchen, a study, a reading corner — where curtains feel like too much and a bare window feels like too little — the Roman shade is always the answer.</p>
        <p>Order your space. Order your mind.</p>
      </div>
      <ul class="ll-nest-benefits">
        <li>Clean architectural fold — visual calm</li>
        <li>Light filtering &amp; blackout options</li>
        <li>Cordless &amp; motorised available</li>
        <li>Perfect for kitchens, studies &amp; small spaces</li>
        <li>Custom sized — no gaps, no guessing</li>
        <li>Linen, cotton &amp; blended fabrics</li>
      </ul>
      <!-- JOYDECO AFFILIATE LINK — replace YOUR_REF with AWIN tracking ref once live -->
      <a href="https://joydeco.com/collections/roman-shades-1?ref=YOUR_REF" class="ll-nest-cta" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Shop Roman Shades →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══ FREE SOLVES STRIP ══ -->
<section class="ll-nest-freesolves">
  <div class="ll-nest-freesolves-inner">
    <div class="ll-nest-freesolves-eyebrow">✦ Free Solves · Feng Shui Your Space ✦</div>
    <h2>Six things you can do today.<br>For free. Right now.</h2>
    <p class="ll-nest-freesolves-intro">
      You don't need to redecorate. You need to edit.<br>
      Feng shui is not mystical — it is the art of intentional arrangement.<br>
      Here is where to start.
    </p>
    <div class="ll-nest-tips-grid">
      <div class="ll-nest-tip-card">
        <span class="ll-nest-tip-number">01</span>
        <div class="ll-nest-tip-title">Clear the entry</div>
        <p class="ll-nest-tip-body">In feng shui, the entrance is where all energy enters. One cleared, welcoming surface changes the feeling of your whole home. Remove what doesn't belong there. It takes six minutes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ll-nest-tip-card">
        <span class="ll-nest-tip-number">02</span>
        <div class="ll-nest-tip-title">Dress your windows</div>
        <p class="ll-nest-tip-body">Bare windows are an unfinished sentence. Even a simple sheer — the softening of the light — changes the energy of a room from transient to intentional. You are staying. You are making it yours.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ll-nest-tip-card">
        <span class="ll-nest-tip-number">03</span>
        <div class="ll-nest-tip-title">One beautiful thing</div>
        <p class="ll-nest-tip-body">Charity shops. Markets. Your own forgotten shelf. Find one beautiful object and give it a place of honour. Your home should contain things that make you feel something when you see them.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ll-nest-tip-card">
        <span class="ll-nest-tip-number">04</span>
        <div class="ll-nest-tip-title">Ground the room with a rug</div>
        <p class="ll-nest-tip-body">In feng shui, a rug anchors the energy of a space and defines intention. A floating sofa with nothing underneath it says the room hasn't decided what it is. A rug says: this is a place where we land.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ll-nest-tip-card">
        <span class="ll-nest-tip-number">05</span>
        <div class="ll-nest-tip-title">Add one living thing</div>
        <p class="ll-nest-tip-body">A plant. Even a small one. Living energy in a space — something breathing, growing — shifts the entire atmosphere. A pothos. A palm. A single stem of eucalyptus in a glass of water. That is enough.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ll-nest-tip-card">
        <span class="ll-nest-tip-number">06</span>
        <div class="ll-nest-tip-title">Light something</div>
        <p class="ll-nest-tip-body">A candle in the evening is one of the oldest signals humans have used to mark the shift from day to rest. It tells your nervous system: this part of the day is different. It costs almost nothing. It changes everything.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══ 4: RUGS ══ -->
<section class="ll-nest-section">
  <div class="ll-nest-inner reverse">
    <div class="ll-nest-img-block">
      <img src="/images/joydeco-rug.webp" alt="JoyDeco Area Rug" class="ll-nest-img" loading="lazy">
      <p class="ll-nest-caption">In classical feng shui, a rug represents Earth energy — the element of stability, nourishment and groundedness. A room without a rug is energetically unanchored. Place it so all furniture legs touch the edge, or at minimum the front legs: this connects each piece to the room's foundation.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ll-nest-content">
      <div class="ll-nest-eyebrow">Ground</div>
      <h2 class="ll-nest-title">Area Rugs</h2>
      <p class="ll-nest-tagline">A room without a rug is a room that hasn't committed.</p>
      <div class="ll-nest-body">
        <p>There is a reason a well-rugged room feels so much more like a home.</p>
        <p>It is not just warmth, though there is warmth. It is not just softness underfoot, though that matters too. It is that a rug makes a decision. It says: this is the room. This is where we gather. This is where we land.</p>
        <p>Floating furniture — a sofa with nothing underneath, a table hovering — registers as unsettled. As temporary. As not quite arrived.</p>
        <p>A rug grounds your space. It absorbs sound, defines zones, adds the layer of texture that a room needs to feel finished. Not decorated. Finished.</p>
        <p>This is the foundation. Everything else sits on top of it.</p>
      </div>
      <ul class="ll-nest-benefits">
        <li>Anchors furniture &amp; defines zones</li>
        <li>Absorbs sound — quieter, calmer rooms</li>
        <li>Adds warmth underfoot &amp; visually</li>
        <li>Natural &amp; blended fibre options</li>
        <li>Multiple sizes — from accent to room-sized</li>
        <li>Earths the feng shui energy of any space</li>
      </ul>
      <!-- JOYDECO AFFILIATE LINK — replace YOUR_REF with AWIN tracking ref once live -->
      <a href="https://joydeco.com/collections/rugs-1?ref=YOUR_REF" class="ll-nest-cta" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Shop Area Rugs →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══ 5: THROWS ══ -->
<section class="ll-nest-section">
  <div class="ll-nest-inner">
    <div class="ll-nest-img-block">
      <img src="/images/joydeco-throw.webp" alt="JoyDeco Throw Blanket" class="ll-nest-img" loading="lazy">
      <p class="ll-nest-caption">Texture is the most underestimated element of interior design. The human eye reads textural contrast as depth and warmth — a monochromatic room with varied textures reads as more sophisticated than a colourful room with flat, uniform surfaces. A throw does more visual work than most people realise.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ll-nest-content">
